SUMMARY:Conservation @ Home: Spring Ephemerals
DESCRIPTION:Have you ever wondered how some wildflowers bloom while the ground is still cold and the air feels like winter? Join University of Illinois Extension for this free one-hour webinar to explore Illinois’ native spring ephemerals and their vital role in supporting early-season pollinators. Learn how to plant and care for these resilient woodland flowers to bring early color and habitat into your landscape.
URL:https://fpdcc.com/event/conservation-home-spring-ephemerals/
CATEGORIES:Conservation@Home,Education,Gardening,Virtual
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://fpdcc.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/conservation-at-home-evaluation-sep16.jpg
LOCATION:https://extension.illinois.edu/events/2026-03-21-conservationhomes-2026-spring-ephemerals-webinar
END:VEVENT
