SUMMARY:Women in the Wilds
DESCRIPTION:Overview:\nCelebrate women in conservation and the natural sciences with presentations\, hands-on activities and information promoting job and volunteer opportunities. \nSchedule:\n\n10 am: Volunteer panel discussion\n11 am: “Stillness in the Wild” mindfulness and meditation workshop (limited spots available)\n1 pm: “Meet Our Birds” program\n12 pm – 2pm: Conservation “Show & Tell” featuring volunteers from University of Illinois Extension\, Forest Preserve District of Cook County\, and more\n\nDrop in for:\n\nJob and volunteer opportunity fair\nAnimal programs\nGuided walks\nConservation education activities\nCrafts\nFace painting\n\nFeatured vendors:\n\nForest Press Co\nZemi Coffee\nThe Urban Canopy\nSkunk Cabbage BooksEat Em Up Catering
URL:https://fpdcc.com/event/women-in-the-wilds/
LOCATION:Sand Ridge Nature Center\, 15891 S Paxton Ave\, South Holland\, IL\, 60473\, United States
CATEGORIES:Animal Ambassador,Education,History & Culture,South Cook County,Volunteer,Wellness in the Woods
